## Conditional Validations

### Using :if and :unless

```ruby
class Article < ApplicationRecord
  # Only validate when published
  validates :published_at, presence: true, if: :published?
  
  # Multiple conditions with proc
  validates :excerpt, presence: true, if: -> { published? && featured? }
  
  # With method name
  validates :body, length: { minimum: 500 }, if: :long_form?
  
  # Using unless (opposite of if)
  validates :draft_notes, presence: true, unless: :published?
  
  private
  
  def published?
    status == 'published'
  end
  
  def long_form?
    article_type == 'long_form'
  end
end
```

### Context-Based Validations

```ruby
class User < ApplicationRecord
  # Only on create
  validates :password, presence: true, on: :create
  
  # Only on update
  validates :current_password, presence: true, on: :update
  
  # Custom context
  validates :admin_notes, presence: true, on: :admin_update
end

# Usage
user.save(context: :admin_update)
```

